The paper deals with the transfer theorem underlying adaptive data analysis, which is a fundamental concept in differential privacy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, the paper also involves statistical queries and generalization guarantees, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses information theory and probability theory to derive its results, which are areas covered by the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, and cs.AI.
